Thanks Shrike, I can definitely fix that. I was under the impression that cognitohazards were things like pictures that you see and then they affect you, which is why I assumed it was memetics instead. If someone else can confirm what Shrike says I'll go ahead and change it.

It's definitely one where you probably have to experienced the outright madness in real life, when it comes to people's tastes in how to make tea (I'm British). I've seen plenty of arguments first hand on the subject ranging from cheerful disagreements to people actually getting peed off and getting in a huff about it! Hence why it will probably resonate most with people from countries like the UK and New Zealand who drink a lot of tea with milk.

The serious tone came about as it was originally going to be a  SCP, albeit a silly one. There are plenty in the database already such as the evil robot who is totally useless. Maybe it is more suitable as that. But a few people told me they thought it should be a Joke SCP instead so I went down that route for the rest of it. It's certainly not going to be to everyone's tastes as its quite dry humour.

If you think it should be resubmitted as a normal SCP with a bit of toning down on the bits you suggested, I'm all ears!

Thanks for the feedback.








