http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-578967

See aelanna's post in that thread. She also links to the tag guide.

Basically, a cognitohazard is a thing that affects your thoughts (or more) if you sense it an any way. In this case, by making people . The effects themselves are cognitohazardous. I guess :p

An infohazard is a thing that affects your thoughts/actions if you even know about it. But, being told about the dapper gentleman has no effect right?

A memetic affect is any mental effect that's contagious. The contagion itself is the meme.

These are not mutually exclusive. The cognitohazardous effect of a cognitohazard could also be memetic. But it doesn't seem to be in this case.

If it affects your actions, it's also a compulsion. But, in this case, is it:

1. You actually kinda think he's an irritating friend or relative, and the way you treat him is simply a result of that?

2. You treat him like that despite knowing it's not the appropriate way to react to him, because he's a total stranger.





