I thoroughly enjoyed this. Regarding the Barry mentioned, there's a popular brand of Irish tea called Barry's.

I am relying on memory for this, but the original justification for pouring the milk before the tea was to minimize the chance that hot tea poured into a delicate room-temperature teacup would shatter it. Room temperature in XIXth century Britain was about 68°F/ 20°C.







